comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-11T12:02:18.272Z",codex-root,"Evidence: public SDK now exports plan contracts and PmClient façade methods for every plan subcommand. Focused plan/SDK/contracts suites pass; typecheck, zero-duplication, static quality, token-budget, docs, and contracts snapshot gates pass. Packed-tarball temp consumer initialized a tracker, created a two-step plan, materialized a Task, and verified enriched title/type/parent/tags/from_step output. Full coverage run was contaminated by an accidental concurrent duplicate and surfaced pre-existing date-version sync assertions; all functional SDK/plan tests passed, and the unrelated assertions are fixed under pm-pmmv. Full clean coverage rerun remains required before closure."
  "2026-07-11T13:26:32.667Z",codex-root,"Final evidence: public SDK exposes every typed plan workflow primitive; governed materialization preserves required custom fields and returns confirmation-rich projections. Final installed-tarball temp consumer created/reordered/annotated/materialized a three-step plan. Full coverage passed 271 files / 5,541 tests / exact 100/100/100/100; lint, static quality, contracts, docs, security, health, history drift, and generator sync gates pass."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-10T21:30:53.590Z",maintainer-agent,"Implementation slicing 2026-07-10 (grounded in current src state). Already public — do NOT redo: the pm_plan MCP surface and generic plan action dispatch; profile *planning* (planProfileApplication from core/profile/profile-plan.ts) is a different domain and already exported. The actual gap: the ENTIRE plan workflow lives in src/cli/commands/plan.ts (1,796 lines) — there is no src/core/plan module at all, making this the largest single-module promotion left in the epic besides test.ts. Plan is also the agent-harness surface (Codex/Claude/Cursor-style planning), so primitive-level promotion is what makes SDK-embedded planning harnesses possible without shelling out. Suggested slices: S1 plan document model + step lifecycle primitives (~90m) — create with stepTitle, step transitions, plan read model. S2 plan annotation primitives (~60m) — dependencies/decisions/discoveries; shapes should mirror the pm-zwpp S1 annotation kernel — coordinate so plan does not grow a second annotation engine. S3 validation + materialization primitives (~60m) — materialize creates real items and MUST consume the shipped lifecycle primitives (pm-98cz) rather than private paths; this is the primitive-level fix site for pm-qd2h / GH-452 (materialize dead-ends on required-on-create custom fields) and pm-ypha / GH-453 (materialize --json omits title/type/parent) — coordinate with both, do not duplicate their fixes. S4 typed PmClient facades + SDK reference docs/tests (~30m), result shapes matching runAction oracle. Order: strictly S1 -> S2 -> S3 -> S4 (each layer consumes the previous one)."
files[2]{path,scope,note}:
